<br>
I took a group down to the shroom king on sat sun and mon. Sat, I asked a group to join me for reets juggs. I thought it would be cool! So instead, 2 groups come down. We take 3 groups, get to reets juggs, an d whup, king spawns behind us. Get your freakin minds off king. &quot;Omg phat lewt.&quot; WEe are going to do juggs reets! Then guildmembers on the raid and break down and start arguing about experience! WTF!Of course you try and share, but you do not do so at the cost of letting mobs go down slow, we still need everyone fighting. You don't sit out because you are trying to share experience. Spoiled brats. You need to hit that fearplane wout a cleric or enchanter, and learn what teamwork , or taking it for the team is all about. Where you set your mind to a goal, and you get the job done no matter what. <br>
<br>
The raid degenerated as people clamored and bickered for experience, and for going to get phat lewt off the king. Look kids, he is rare. But not so rare that if you camp him, he will not spawn! Most of you got guilds, if you truly are about helping each other, go frreaking camp it. Instead, the very words I hear from members of guilds are , &quot;my guild won't help me, are you kidding?&quot; or, &quot;I can't with my guild.&quot; Is it because you are all greedy? Sheesh paranoia.<br>
<br>
I tried again on sunday night, with 2 groups. We get to juggs, and king spawns! bah. The raid breaks down as people clamor to go back and hit king. Forget the damn king. &quot;I need an item off him.&quot; &quot;Others could use the tunic too.&quot;<br>
&quot;You are just being selfish because you havee a tunic.&quot; Look kids, I worked for mine. And not one damn person among you would say , &quot;sure shaere come along, we will get you this xxitemxx.&quot; Im selfish? Because I am sticking to our objective? Phat monk lewtz at reets juggs, wtf. <br>
<br>
We had been having problems with experience, when upon entering illis jail I find the enchanter in other group hadn't been ressed at zone, because they wanted a 56 res. So we decide once at zone out, I'll go out and drag it down. Well, as we move deeper, I find the ench is now at zone! Because they got a res and then they leave, saying, &quot;too much trouble to get bck down.&quot; Wtf is that nonsense! So we have a sham come down to replace her. Now experience is one sided. Now because it is dumb to have people not nuking, letting mobs live longer, I try many combinations oif rearranging groups. I ask my druid to nuke a little now. That didnt work, so I switch their wiz and my dru. Well, now it starts to even up, then the dru starts nuking OOM on each pull. Because they want exp for their group? And when I ask for a buff from them, I am told, &quot;get your sham in your group to buff you, I am nuking for exp in mine.&quot; Now experience is all one sided. Wtf is this nonsense. <br>
<br>
This going on the same time people are crying to go do king for phat lewt.<br>
<br>
<br>
I am going to tell you how it is people, something long overdue from me, a rant that will be replied to as peoples insecurity and ignorance fuel their flames.<br>
<br>
Greed underlies everything I see in this game. Some of you talk the talk about sharing, but only to an extent. What i see sickens me with this Me me me me me attitude.<br>
<br>
First off, whose business is it if some guild chooses to allocate loot among guild members in any way they see fit. Granted there are mnany ambiguous systems and fugged up things that happen, but the point system is clear. If you aren't in the guild it may suck if you go, because you have been demoted to a first raid status, despite previous history.<br>
<br>
Part of this is fostered by greed and paranoia. Guilds are cool. The problem with them is that they become exclusive little cliques or societies, cut off from others. Why is this you ask? Well, from MM comes the majority of drinal players. From a guild run server. A guild would own the server, all loot for them, damned to the rest of you. So the only way to fight this &quot;evil&quot; as some call it, is forming your own guild capable of competition. The problem I see is they become the very monster they seek to combat.<br>
<br>
Now there are exceptions to any rule, and all generalizations, including this one are false. But as a rule, I notice this attitude pervading drinal where we are keeping to us and our own and ignoring others. Why? Greed paranoia. Dare let someone not in your little circle in, and they may have the gall to ask or expect loot that could be YOURS. Ask that leader of said raid if there any other mages. Heck, the point system rocks, but I see jealousy and anger fostered around it. &quot;I'm next in line for xxclasxx bp.&quot; &quot;Man, that guy sucks and he gets the next xxlootxx.&quot;<br>
<br>
Oh, and to set this record straight. I am tired of players telling me they are experienced. When your hate raid consists of a southwest corner farm, when you didn't do planes till you were post 50, when you have 45 days played, you ain't got experience for shit yet so stuff it. Some players can take one raid, and learn fast, and are good to go. Most of you need to learn by rote, so after `50 trains you finally learn what the hell BACK UP and nothing else means. If you were truly experienced, you would know enough that on any given raid you listen to said &quot;leader's&quot; &quot;orders&quot;.  Because not doing so only creates problems.<br>
<br>
&quot;You treat experienced players like newbies.&quot; Well you know what, I don't if you are and you act like it. You act like a newbie, or make a newbie mistake, I tend to let you hear it. But as a general rule I have noticed the majority of players on drinal are from mm. A server where most didn't get the chances to do planes or whatever as much as they may have wanted. I notice in comparison to what I see from tunarians(what a word), underequiiped and inexperienced. Im not saying you're all newbie warriors in crafted. But your 45 played days, post 50, means jack to me. You were spoiled. Grown up in a server that sold trak bp's? wtf. Powerlvled to 50 or beyond. Had all this nifty kunark stuff to make life easier.<br>
<br>
is it your fault ? NO. The game is sposed to be fun, and relaxing to an extent, not some great ordeal. But don't sit there with 50 played days and your quest armor and tell me I am treating experienced players like newbies. Relatively speaking, you ARE. I can tell because when I say, &quot;sit here&quot;, instead of simply sitting there, we get defensive. We say, &quot;Boy he is rude, he thinks he can tell me what to do.&quot; There is a damn reason for sitting there, and especially it boggles me that players who have never seen a  jugg before can refuse or think they know any better than someone who has! If I tell you to move, and to sit here, it is not because I am rude, treating you like a newbie.<br>
<br>
It is because we need to move, and to sit there, for specific reasons. All of your vaunted west wall experience in hate doesn't impress me. Experienced players know what to do, and in absence of being absolutely positive, you listen and follow. In situations you have never been in, you listen to those that have. You do not cop some attitude and not cooperate, because YOU are experienced. I laugh at your experience. You want arrogance? I  place my time logged in one plane, pick it, versus your /played time. Sky plane, maybe you got me beat. But Give it a rest. Some people think they know, with 15 hate raids under their belt, and 10 dragons. <br>
<br>
You have been coddled, spoiled, and some act like it. <br>
<br>
